Subject: in_dxf: derive SORTENTSTABLE.block_owner from the ownership chain

An empty SORTENTSTABLE carries no explicit block_owner in DXF. The importer
then misread the table's object owner (its extension DICTIONARY) as
block_owner, so block_owner pointed at a DICTIONARY instead of the
BLOCK_HEADER whose entities the table sorts. AutoCAD/ODA flag the owning
block ("Invalid input <AcDbBlockTableRecord>"). block_owner is the owner of
the extension dictionary that owns the table, so derive it (owner->owner) in
a SORTENTSTABLE postprocess; a non-empty table whose explicit block_owner
already differs from its owner is trusted as-is. 254 unit tests green.

NOTE: this corrects block_owner fidelity but does NOT by itself clear the
non-fatal "<AcDbBlockEnd> needs recovery" recovery warning on casa bueno's
_ARCHTICK block, which has a deeper, not-minimally-reproducible cause.

Co-authored-by: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>

--- a/src/in_dxf.c
+++ b/src/in_dxf.c
@@ add dxf_postprocess_SORTENTSTABLE + dispatch in new_object tail
